Overall Recommendations:

1. Improve the user interface (UI) and ensure a seamless user experience across different devices and screen sizes.
2. Enhance error handling by providing informative error messages to guide users in case of input errors or failures.
3. Implement unit tests, integration tests, and end-to-end tests to cover different features.
4. Regularly gather user feedback and conduct user testing to identify areas for improvement and prioritize new feature development.
5. Maintain a strong focus on data security and privacy, ensuring that user information is adequately protected.






